Package com.advertisementproject.campaignservice.controller

Class CampaignController

java.lang.Object
com.advertisementproject.campaignservice.controller.CampaignController
@RestController
public class CampaignController
extends java.lang.Object
Controller for campaigns management. Uses CampaignService and CompanyService to fulfill the requests. Different endpoints have different access restrictions defined by the Zuul Gateway application.

  • Method Details

    • getAllCampaigns

      @GetMapping("/all") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.util.List<Campaign>> getAllCampaigns()
      Endpoint for getting all campaigns for all companies. Should only be available for ADMIN users.
      Returns:
      Response entity with a list of all campaigns in the database.

    • getAllPublishedCampaigns

      @GetMapping("/all/published") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.util.List<Campaign>> getAllPublishedCampaigns()
      Endpoint for getting all published campaigns with limited information. Should be open to all users.
      Returns:
      Response entity with a list of all published campaigns in the database with limited information.
      Json View:
      restricts the information so that discount codes and company ids are hidden in the response.

    • getCampaignsByCompanyId

      @GetMapping public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.util.List<Campaign>> getCampaignsByCompanyId​(@RequestHeader("userId") java.util.UUID companyId)
      Endpoint for getting all campaigns for the currently logged in company.
      Parameters:
      companyId - the id for the currently logged in company user, provided by Zuul Gateway in the header.
      Returns:
      Response entity with a list of all campaigns and custom response headers for the logged in company in the database.

    • deleteAllCampaignsByCompanyId

      @DeleteMapping public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.String> deleteAllCampaignsByCompanyId​(@RequestHeader("userId") java.util.UUID companyId)
      Endpoint for deleting all campaigns for the currently logged in company.
      Parameters:
      companyId - the id for the currently logged in company user, provided by Zuul Gateway in the header.
      Returns:
      Response entity with the message that all campaigns have been deleted for the companyId provided.

    • createCampaign

      @PostMapping public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Campaign> createCampaign​(@Valid @RequestBody @Valid CampaignRequest campaignRequest, @RequestHeader("userId") java.util.UUID companyId)
      Endpoint for a company to create a new campaign.
      Parameters:
      campaignRequest - campaign request object that allows the client to specify what information the campaign should include. Some fields are optional and some are validated for not being null.
      companyId - the id for the currently logged in company user, provided by Zuul Gateway in the header.
      Returns:
      Response entity returning the newly created campaign which has been saved in the database.

    • getCampaign

      @GetMapping("/{campaignId}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Campaign> getCampaign​(@PathVariable java.util.UUID campaignId, @RequestHeader("userId") java.util.UUID companyId)
      Endpoint for getting a specific campaign.
      Parameters:
      campaignId - the id for the requested campaign.
      companyId - the id for the currently logged in company user, provided by Zuul Gateway in the header.
      Returns:
      Response entity with the campaign that was requested.

    • updateCampaign

      @PutMapping("/{campaignId}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Campaign> updateCampaign​(@PathVariable java.util.UUID campaignId, @RequestBody CampaignRequest campaignRequest, @RequestHeader("userId") java.util.UUID companyId)
      Endpoint for updating a specific campaign.
      Parameters:
      campaignId - the id of the campaign to be updated.
      campaignRequest - request object containing the fields that should be changed. Only the provided fields will validated and then changed if valid.
      companyId - the id for the currently logged in company user, provided by Zuul Gateway in the header.
      Returns:
      Response entity with the updated campaign.

    • deleteCampaign

      @DeleteMapping("/{campaignId}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.String> deleteCampaign​(@PathVariable java.util.UUID campaignId, @RequestHeader("userId") java.util.UUID companyId)
      Endpoint for deleting a specific campaign.
      Parameters:
      campaignId - the id of the campaign to be deleted.
      companyId - the id for the currently logged in company user, provided by Zuul Gateway in the header.
      Returns:
      Response entity with the message that the specific campaign has been deleted.

    • getDiscountCode

      @GetMapping("/discount-code/{campaignId}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.String> getDiscountCode​(@PathVariable java.util.UUID campaignId)
      Endpoint for logged in users to retrieve the discount code for a specific campaign.
      Parameters:
      campaignId - the id of the campaign to retrieve the discount code from.
      Returns:
      Response entity with the requested discount code.
